  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>
      <hi>M. D.</hi> Esquire To his good Friend, <hi>T. V.</hi>
   </head>
   <l>WHat Thou do'st teach, by others heretofore</l>
   <l>Hath likewise bin. But yet by no man more</l>
   <l>To the true life. That by thy godly care,</l>
   <l>Thou and thine Authour equally doe share.</l>
   <l>Thou praisest him Translating, but if he</l>
   <l>Vnderstood English he would more praise thee.</l>
   <l>Thou to our Nation ha'st his Doctrine showne,</l>
   <l>Which to our vulgar else had not beene knowne;</l>
   <l>As much by this thou get'st as ere he wanne:</l>
   <l>
      <hi>England,</hi> praise <hi>Vicars, Dantsk</hi> her <hi>Keckerman.</hi>
   </l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Mich. Drayton.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
